<item>
            <title>[DERBY-3782] Client Configuration.java imports engine class  org.apache.derby.iapi.services.info.JVMInfo </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3782</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The client code (org.apache.derby.client.am.Configuration) imports the engine class org.apache.derby.iapi.services.info.JVMInfo.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will make two copies of the class in derby.jar and derbyclient.jar which can cause problems if mixed version jars are used and  I think may cause jar sealing issues as well.&lt;br/&gt;
Until we have a good framework for sharing code between engine and client, the client shouldn&apos;t import engine classes.&lt;/p&gt;

</description>
